		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>As I understand it, Charisma affects the following:<br><br>1) Prices for buying from/selling to vendors, to a degree. (Also use the Alliance line and, for non-human races, illusions if you don't get the best price with Charisma alone.)<br>2) Resist rate for Mez spells. By this I mean whether or not the spell is resisted outright. As far as I have seen, the duration is a fixed number of seconds and does not have an incremental check, like Charm (or other spells like Root).<br>3) Resist rate for Charm (and Fear).<br>4) Duration of effect for Charm (and Fear) based on an incremental check.<br><br>I'm in the process of trying to balance Charisma, Intelligence, and Mana items, and it's causing a bit of a headache. Add Magic Resist gear (to avoid mezzing yourself in tight quarters) to the mix and it's a wonderful little juggling act.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
